The paper proposes an AI-based design automation framework that integrates topology optimization and deep generative models for generative design. This involves the use of GANs for generating new design options, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves the optimization of engineering performance, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the aesthetics and diversity of generated designs, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR). Overall, the paper's focus on deep learning and generative design makes it most likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category.
